						               													<description>The Game has a board of a part of Europe where the main battles of WWII occurred. There are 12 cities and 6 bridges strategically placed.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;This is a game for 2-4 players. Each player has an army of 5 Main Battle Tanks (20 points each), 5 Artillery Pieces (15 points each) and 5 Troops Transport Trucks (10 points each). The units must be placed in their start point accordingly to their color.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In each turn, a player rolls a dice and then can advance their units accordingly. When two or more enemy units reach the same place, a battle can emerge. When the attacker have the same points than the defender, the defender's units return to their starting point, when the attacker have more points, then the defender's units are removed from the board. A player can't attack with less points than the enemy.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;There are 4 ways to win in this game:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;a) Total anihilation of the enemy.&amp;#10;b) Cities occupattion&amp;#10;c) Invading the enemy's starting point&amp;#10;d) Bridges occupation&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
